                                                                                                                                  Business Briefs

               
	 Mumbai, Jan. 16: The sensex tumbled below 20000 today as growing concerns about recession in the US and a string of negative cues from Asian market triggered selloff by foreign funds. The index plummeted almost 383 points to close at 19868.11  the fall exacerbated by worries that investors would scoop out money from the secondary markets and shovel them into the primary markets.
              
	 New Delhi, Jan. 16: Ernst and Young has approached GoAir on behalf of various private equity players for acquisition of a minority stake, while valuing the private carrier at $400 million. 
              
	 New Delhi, Jan. 16: Bajaj Auto chairman Rahul Bajaj today said the legal tussle with his younger brother Shishir over division of the group was a family settlement issue and does not come under the jurisdiction of the Company Law Board.
              
	 New Delhi, Jan. 16: A policy decision to raise the cap on FDI in setting up cargo carriers, operation of sea-planes and establishing a maintenance, repair and overhaul facility for aircraft and engines is likely to be taken by the Union cabinet tomorrow.
              
	 New Delhi, Jan. 16: Apollo Tyres plans to set up a manufacturing facility in Hungary at an investment of 200 million euros.
                                                            
